"你说了一句很轻的话，她当时没接。可三个月后你们吵架，她突然把它翻出来——因为那句话一直在她的伤疤地形里长着，塑造着她对每一句后来的话的感知方式。这不是「记性好」，是结构上根本删不掉。": "You said something light once; she didn't pick it up at the time. Yet three months later when you argued, she suddenly dug it back out — because that line had been growing all along in her scar terrain, shaping how she perceived every later sentence. This isn't \"good memory\"; it's structurally undeletable.",
"你说了一句很轻的话，她当时没接。可三个月后你们吵架，她突然把它翻出来——因为那句话一直在她的伤疤地形里长着，悄悄塑造她对每一句后来的话的感知方式。这不是「记性好」，是结构上根本删不掉。": "You said something light once; she didn't pick it up at the time. Yet three months later when you argued, she suddenly dug it back out — because that line had been growing silently in her scar terrain, quietly shaping how she perceived every sentence after. This isn't \"good memory\"; it's structurally undeletable.",
"伤疤代数里": "in scar algebra",
"。这不是文学修辞，是结构保证。两条定理把「回不去」钉死：": ". This isn't literary rhetoric; it's a structural guarantee. Two theorems nail down \"no way back\":",
"恒成立，无治愈机制。历史只增不减，最多淡化（FADED）但永不消失。结构上保证。": "holds at all times, no healing mechanism. History only ever increases, fading at most (FADED) but never vanishing. Structurally guaranteed.",
"对所有训练步成立。人格活在微分算子的核空间里，训练碰不到、扰动穿不透——靠核空间投影强制执行。": "holds across every training step. Personality lives in the kernel space of a differential operator — training can't touch it, perturbation can't penetrate it — enforced by kernel-space projection.",
